Add a cwd-aware fallback for POSIX path resolution without forcing `chdir.o`.

Upstream wasi-libc keeps cwd-aware path resolution behind the weak
`__wasilibc_find_relpath_alloc()` symbol from `chdir.c`. Programs that never
call `chdir()` do not link that object, so relative paths fall back to the root
preopen. Making the call unconditional fixes the semantics but introduces a new
problem on WASM: direct calls to a missing weak symbol trap.

Keep the weak-symbol fast path, but add an always-linked fallback in
`preopens.c` that resolves relative paths against `getcwd()` and reuses
`__wasilibc_find_abspath()`. `posix.c` uses that fallback whenever the weak
helper is absent. This makes `curl -o local.txt` and `curl -O` work correctly
for ordinary programs without dragging `chdir.o` into every binary.

